<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B62165378E8F9442218F8FC" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B62165378E8F9442650F8A5" blockId="18.[136,1452,1490,2092]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B62165378E8F9442699F909" bold="true" box="[189,451,1670,1696]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Nomenclatural notes:</emphasis>
— 
<materialsCitation id="B78E3CD00B62165379B5F944265FF8A5" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3746876303" collectionCode="P, K, NY, LE" country="United States of America" location="Therefore" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="syntype">
Schumann (1910) designated the collection Riedel 2021 as type from 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6216537D42F94422FEF909" authorityName="K. Schumann" authorityYear="1891" box="[1303,1444,1670,1696]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riedelii">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6216537D42F94422FEF909" box="[1303,1444,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Sida riedelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, there are 
<specimenCount id="11E0FD040B621653793AF968257DF96D" box="[367,551,1706,1732]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" type="generic">eight specimens</specimenCount>
of this collection, all 
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B6216537B7BF96924C9F96C" box="[814,915,1707,1733]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">syntypes</typeStatus>
, deposited in herbaria 
<collectionCode id="61F7AE480B6216537CCAF96923F4F96C" box="[1183,1198,1707,1733]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="61F7AE480B6216537CE8F969238EF96C" box="[1213,1236,1707,1733]" country="United Kingdom" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15867" name="Royal Botanic Gardens" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" type="Herbarium">K</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="61F7AE480B6216537CB6F9692251F96C" box="[1251,1291,1707,1733]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B6216537D4CF9682265F96D" box="[1305,1343,1706,1732]" name="United States of America" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">US</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectionCode id="61F7AE480B6216537DD7F96922F2F96C" box="[1410,1448,1707,1733]" country="Brazil" name="Servico de Microbiologia e Imunologia" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">LE</collectionCode>
. 
<location id="023960560B62165378DDF90C27A3F941" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:8F4F879B0B62165478DDFA102231FEA9:023960560B62165378DDF90C27A3F941" box="[136,249,1742,1768]" country="United States of America" name="Therefore" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Therefore</location>
, one of the specimens, from the herbarium 
<collectionCode id="61F7AE480B6216537AB3F90D25AFF940" box="[742,757,1743,1769]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
, was designated as a 
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B6216537BB2F90C230BF941" box="[999,1105,1742,1768]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">lectotype</typeStatus>
, because it is representative of the species
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0759368D0B62165378E8F8D42218F8FC" blockId="18.[136,1452,1490,2092]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B62165378E8F8D426CAF899" bold="true" box="[189,400,1814,1840]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B62165379F9F8D4256CF899" authorityName="K. Schumann" authorityYear="1891" box="[428,566,1814,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riedelii">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B62165379F9F8D4256CF899" box="[428,566,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Sida riedelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6216537B25F8D424A5F899" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[880,1023,1814,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6216537B25F8D424A5F899" box="[880,1023,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Sida spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it is distinguished by the hyaline and crumbly dorsal face of its mericarps (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B6216537AE6F8F82417F8FD" box="[691,845,1850,1876]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,190,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[190,1398,190,1896]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. A–E. Sida regnellii. A. Flower. B. Adaxial surface of leaf. C. Branch with flower, leaves and mature schizocarp. D. Habit. E. Branch with leaves and mature schizocarps. F–J. Sida rhombifolia. F, G. Flowers. H. Abaxial surface of leaf. I. Adaxial surface of leaf. J. Branch with mature mericarps. L–P. Sida riedelii. L. Flower. M. Branch with leaves, flower bud and mature mericarp. N.Adaxial surface of leaf. O. Abaxial surface of leaf. P. Branch with tubercle at petiole base. Photographs by Martin Grings and Sérgio A.L. Bordignon (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415507/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Figures 9L–P</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B6216537B02F8F824D3F8FD" box="[855,905,1850,1876]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">14Q</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6216537BCAF8F82302F8FD" author="Schumann, K." box="[927,1112,1850,1876]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" pagination="253 - 456" refId="ref20394" refString="Schumann, K. (1891) Malvaceae I. In: Martius, C. F. P. de, Eichler, A. G. &amp; Urban, I. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis, Vol. 12, pars III. Frid. Fleischer, Lipsiae, pp. 253 - 456, pl. 51 - 80." type="book chapter" year="1891">Schumann 1891</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6216537C31F8F8226CF8FC" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[1124,1334,1850,1877]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" pagination="292 - 333" refId="ref19401" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2005) Malvaceae. In: Bacigalupo, N. M. (Ed.) Flora Ilustrada de Entre-Rios. 6 (4 b). Colecc. Ci. Inst. Nac. Tecnol. Agropecu, pp. 292 - 333." type="book chapter" year="2005">Krapovickas 2005</bibRefCitation>
